result.execSummary:
Ryan R Krueger was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Ryan R Krueger was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Status conference on November 26, 2014 at 01:15 pm.

Case called at 1:54 pm
Defendant Ryan R Krueger in court, in custody with Attorney Yelena Zarwell from the Jefferson County Public Defenders Office. Public Service Special Prosecutor Melanie Flint appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court verifies with the Defendant that the DOB and address listed on the criminal complaint are correct.
Attorney Zarwell informs the Court that the defendant wishes to waive extradition, defendant affirms that he wishes to waive extradition.
Court reviews constitutional rights.
Defendant endorses the waiver form in front of the Court.
Court endorses the Waiver of Extradition form.

Recess: 2;00 pm
